scenario:
The macro expands to a call through the function pointer _metal.common.log_handler. If that handler implementation calls metal_log (the macro) to perform logging, an indirect recursion occurs: log_handler -> metal_log -> log_handler -> ... For example:

static void my_log_handler(int level, const char *fmt, ...) {
    /* ... */
    metal_log(METAL_LOG_ERROR, "handler error"); /* expands to call _metal.common.log_handler */
}

If _metal.common.log_handler is set to my_log_handler, the call chain is my_log_handler -> metal_log -> my_log_handler, which is an indirect self-call and therefore violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.2.
